    "For instance, to reduce the burden on students, only two dimensions from the Pittsburgh Sleep Quality Index were selected to assess sleep quality and daytime dysfunction.",
    "ConclusionIn summary, our findings indicate that poor sleep quality significantly contributes to increased daytime dysfunction in adolescents, which in turn affects social exclusion, self-control abilities and emotion regulation difficulties.",
    "Social exclusion mediates the relationship between sleep quality and emotion regulation difficulties.",
    "This study offers insights for the development of effective interventions aimed at improving sleep and psychological wellbeing in adolescents.Fig. 11Fig.",
